metadata.name: The Abstract Truth III #17
metadata.description:
Moiré patterns meet halftone dots meet cross stitching.

Halftone is a term that can refer to both a technology used in image processing and as the synonym for semitone in music. A jazz musician Oliver Nelson released the album The Blues and the Abstract Truth in 1961. It is considered one of the most significant records of its time. In addition, he wrote Patterns for Improvisation, a hugely popular jazz patterns book. The Moiré pattern design is on the book's cover.

Look out for the FOMO keyboard key to unlock more variations. 
Press 'P' to pause/unpause the animation.

metadata.name: Soft Cell #86
metadata.description:
This work is an homage to relief printmaking. Other artists have explored the kinship between generative art and print using pen plotters and silkscreen. This work attempts to take the concept of a relief print and apply it to a digital canvas.

This art work is produced in layers. For each layer the printing surface or matrix is defined by one set of algorithms. Another set of algorithms then applies the "ink" (imperfectly!) to the matrix. For each layer in turn the matrix is then applied to the canvas.

Press [s] to save a png image of the work.

The work renders at an economical 800x800px. Any edge size may be specified by adding &sz=x to the URL. A print of about 6 inches by 6 inches is recommended, &sz=1800 at 300dpi.

Rust/JS/WASM
Polygon SDF algorithm adapted from Inigo Quilez.

metadata.name: Pigmenta #9
metadata.description:
Pigmenta is a journey through nature's palette. 
Explore chromatic variations and embrace the colorful life of plants.

"What most impress’d me, and will longest remain with me, are these prairies,
These limitless and beautiful landscapes indeed fill me best and most—
Land of sweet-air’d interminable plateaus, the table-lands notched with ravines,
Land of the wild ravine, the lonesome stretch, the silence,
The clear, pure, cool, rarefied nutriment for the lungs.
Sun-down shadows lengthen over the limitless and lonesome prairie,
The peculiar sentiment of moonlight and stars over the great plains,
The receding perspective, and the far circle-line of the horizon all times of day."

Walt Whitman 


--

Created with p5.js

--
- press 'd' to save the PNG image of the current view.
- press 's' to save in high-resolution.

metadata.name: Digital Labyrinth #9
metadata.description: In the depths of a digital realm, a shape-shifting guardian manifests as maze-like patterns contained within geometric boundaries. Stars and colored blocks scatter across its surface like digital memories or mystical waypoints, while its pathways twist and turn in ever-changing patterns. Each appearance brings a unique arrangement, transforming simple lines into complex labyrinths that could be ancient seals, quantum maps, or portals to unexplored dimensions.

metadata.name: Eternal Shards #7
metadata.description: In the void between time and memory, there exists a realm where fragments of forgotten lives drift in silent harmony. These Eternal Shards—crystalline echoes of joy, sorrow, and stillness—hover in a delicate balance, bound by threads of light that pulse with the weight of what once was. Some glow fiercely as if resisting their inevitable fade; others stand dormant, their edges dulled by the erosion of years. Scattered across this boundless expanse, they form constellations of meaning—dense clusters of shared moments, sparse trails of solitary thoughts, or tangled webs of intertwined fates. A wanderer who stumbles into this space might see their own past reflected in the shards’ silent dance, a mosaic of what endures and what slips away, forever caught in a single, unshifting breath.

metadata.name: Waves of Whimsy #15
metadata.description:
A flowing tapestry of random wavy lines in a vibrant, unpredictable dance of colors and connections.
Story: In a distant realm where the winds of creativity blow freely, Waves of Whimsy was born from the playful hands of an artist seeking to capture the essence of chaos. The lines ripple like rivers across a canvas sky, each refresh revealing a new tale of spontaneity. It’s the first whisper of a world where art knows no bounds, a sketch of dreams painted with the lightest touch of code.
The art is made with pure p5js code. Press 's' or 'S' to save it as a .png image.

metadata.name: Elswhere #190
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: Elevation #63
metadata.description:
There’s so much more to our world than what we are able to perceive, let alone understand. Will we ever be able to even fully understand ourselves?

–

Elevation is a series of 320 generative elevation drawings of imaginary structures. It is a reminder of the limits of our consciousness, and an ode to the manifold nuances that lie beyond what we can perceive, beyond what we even can imagine.

As a generative artist, I aim to elevate my own consciousness with the help of the machine. I welcome algorithms and randomness into the creation of my works, taking full control, and intentionally giving it away, always seeking to expand my imagination. For as humans alone, we remain limited to our own edifice of thought, and often fail to free ourselves from the visible, mundane world.

Both are present in Elevation: the visible and the imaginary, the mundane and the transcendent, the solid and the fragile. Where an architect’s elevation drawing marks the transition from the thought world into the visible world, Elevation remains in-between, depicting both the idea of an imaginary structure, and the structure itself.

–

Elevation is intended for print. All holders of an Elevation NFT will be able to order the corresponding signed print in the respective paper format via andreasrau.eu/elevation. Press [s] to save the image as displayed or [p] to generate a print-ready PNG image at 300 dpi. This might take a while, depending on paper format and your hardware.

–

Elevation
p5.js, glsl, html, css
Andreas Rau, 2022
